{"key":"processedPost-7338956","value":{"id":7338956,"first":7338075,"last":7338956,"when":1188218839,"utime":"08/27/07 03:47 PM","content":"Use a timer so the humidifier runs no more than a minute or two at a time, with five or so minutes between cycles.  You get moisture buildup when the coolmist throws out water faster than the air can absorb it.  Short cycling with a timer prevents that problem.  As you're tweaking the system, lay wax paper over your substrates to protect them from too much water.<br />RR","title":"Re: Mycellium covered in dew. Coolmist in greenhouse."}}